title: Addressing My Mental Health.. Selling My House and Getting Help
description:
There has been so many major life changes for me this year and I'm ready to share them all with you.
It's time to address my mental health and be very transparent. I've had so many silent personal struggles, public feuds and ALOT of mental trauma. Caused by ME, my past actions and people from my past. I've had TOO MUCH loss and have been slowly healing.

It's time to also say goodbye to California for awhile.. I'm selling my giant house in LA, I've donated and sold all my clothes and I'm starting the next chapter of my life. Please listen with an open heart and mind. Thank you to everyone who has stood by me through all the success AND the ugly. I love you so much. If you are struggling with mental health issues or depression, NEVER feel ashamed to ask for help. I waited too long and I'm grateful every day for making the choice to heal.

title: MY NEW BARBIE BMW i8 | Jeffree Star [4K Ultra HD]
description:
THIS VIDEO CAN BE VIEWED IN 4K! [Ultra HD] - HEY EVERYONE! Today I'm putting down the makeup brushes and taking you to my home in Calabasas where I give a tour of my *NEW* Barbie custom pink BMW i8! The design was created by the wizards at West Coast Customs! (Thanks guy, you SLAYED this!!) They custom made this shade of pink for this car and I was so stunned when I saw it for the first time! Beside being obsessed with highlighters and lipsticks, I LOVE sports cars and have been a car fanatic since I was a kid! 

For my birthday last month, I bought this beautiful BMW i8! In this video, I go for a drive and talk about some of my past... getting into a car accident and starting from nothing. My first car I ever had when I graduated high school, was a 1991 Nissan Sentra that 2 people hit and almost totaled... later on in life,  I would drive that beat up old car to freelance makeup jobs and hustle to make rent money and $ to eat... It's crazy that 10 years later my entire life has changed. I never gave up on my dreams and never let anyone tell me "NO" - Your dreams can be a reality... But the road to get there will not alway she pleasant or fun. I'd never give up all of my struggles and experiences. It's made me into the person I am today.

Thank you for making 2016 such an incredible journey and welcoming me on YouTube! It's been an amazing first year as a "YouTuber" as they say haha Can't wait to see what 17 brings us... LOVE YOU. I could never say that enough... XOXO

title: DIOR 'ROUGE' LIPSTICKS: Review & Swatches | Jeffree Star
description:
OH HI... I filmed this video last week before I dyed my hair darker! Who's ready of another round of lip swatches?? Today I'm testing out DIOR'S new lipstick line ROUGE DIOR. I try out 6 of the matte shades and put them to the test! Are they worth $35???
My final thoughts: They wore for a good 4-5 hours before they noticeably started to fade! I touched up 6 hours later and after eating dinner! The formula is light weight and you forget you're wearing anything... But I wish every shade had the same formula!! Something I hate: When some shades are amazing, while others flop... But sometimes pigments and formulas don't always mix and brands have to compromise. All in all... I'm a fan!

title: THE JEFFREE STAR TATTOO DIARIES: PART 1
description:
This video was shot in ULTRA HD 4K! It will look intense and brings out crazy detail! I tried it for the first time so let me know your thoughts...I've never talked about my tattoos until now. I've been collecting them for 12 years and they are a part of my life forever. My entire body is covered in over 100 portraits, memories, names and some of my favorite things, movies, family and pets... Some stories are funny, while some are sad and really personal... Thank you to all my subscribers of pushing me to start this series! Since I have so many, I thought I would start with different portions of my body. In Part 1, I go through my entire front, from my neck, all the way to below my stomach. Every tattoo you see on this video, except one,  was done by Kat Von D. I tell some candid stories and go down memory lane...

title: HAIR TRANSPLANT SURGERY | Jeffree Star (GRAPHIC CONTENT!)
description:
üíâüíâüíâ This video contains "graphic content" - meaning, you can see needles and blood! If you are uncomfortable, DON'T WATCH... or smoke a blunt and come back in 5 minutes! ** THIS IS MY EXPERIENCE getting hair transplant surgery to fix my hair line and widow's peak! My amazing doctor, Dr. Craig L. Ziering and his team transformed me and made me feel so comfortable! Getting ANY type of surgery is nerve-wrecking and can be scary but I was so excited to fix what I've been wanting to change for so long!

What exactly is "Hair Transplantation"??? It's the ONLY permanent solution for hair loss. During hair transplant surgery, you are both the donor and the recipient during the procedure with hair being removed from the donor zone in the back of your head where your hair is genetically programmed to grow for life and being transplanted into the balding and thinning areas of your scalp.

title: JEFFREE STAR & NATHAN TRAVEL TO: MAUI, HAWAII
description:
I think I found my new favorite place... Sometimes it's hard to break yourself away from work. I'm a Scorpio... and I'm OBSESSED with working. I'm always creating art, working on my cosmetics brand, hanging out with my 3 Pomeranians or being a wifey with Nathan (haha) Sometimes I forgot to take a BREAK FROM LIFE for a second!! We all need our brains to take a REST and RECHARGE!! It's important to reflect on the changes and let ourselves experience accomplishments. Never take a single day for granted! So my best friend/assistant Brandy, Nathan and Christian (my videographer) took a week trip to Maui, Hawaii to explore and escape our California madness!
